description: Ex-Union minister P P Choudhary will lead the joint parliamentary committee (JPC) on the "one nation, one election" bills. The 31-member JPC includes first-time MPs Priyanka Gandhi Vadra, Anil Baluni, Sambit Patra, and Bansuri Swaraj. The committee will examine the two bills introduced in the Lok Sabha, proposing simultaneous Lok Sabha and state assembly elections.

description: Home Minister Amit Shah accused Congress of doctoring his Rajya Sabha speech and spreading falsehoods after being exposed as anti-Ambedkar, anti-Constitution, and anti-reservation. description: Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal announced a new healthcare initiative, 'Sanjeevani,' promising free treatment for all Delhi residents over 60 at state-run and private facilities if re-elected. The scheme will utilize a card system, with registration beginning soon. This counters the central government's Ayushman Bharat scheme, which Delhi hasn't implemented.

description: India and China's Special Representatives held their first talks in five years, marking significant progress in normalizing ties.  They affirmed the recent border disengagement agreement, discussed maintaining peace, and agreed on a roadmap for improving relations.  Resuming the Kailash Mansarovar pilgrimage and boosting cross-border cooperation were also key outcomes.

description: The Chicago Bears' season is spiraling downward after a devastating loss to the Vikings. Players like Jaquan Brisker and Cole Kmet are openly expressing their frustrations with the team's performance. description: Parliamentary proceedings were disrupted by heated protests from the opposition, accusing Home Minister Amit Shah of insulting B.R. Ambedkar. Prime Minister Modi defended Shah, dismissing the resignation demands as theatrics and accusing the opposition of spreading falsehoods.
title: Ambedkar row: Govt, opposition face off over Amit Shah remarks

description: BJP MLC Ram Shinde filed his nomination for Maharashtra Legislative Council chairperson, accompanied by CM Fadnavis and Deputy CM Ajit Pawar. Eknath Shinde's absence signals a setback for Shiv Sena, which sought the post for Neelam Gorhe. Shinde's likely unopposed victory gives BJP control of both legislative houses.

description: The United States imposed sanctions on Pakistan's National Development Complex (NDC) and three associated companies for contributing to the country's long-range ballistic missile program.  The sanctions aim to curb proliferation, targeting entities involved in developing missiles, including the SHAHEEN series, potentially capable of carrying nuclear warheads. Pakistan's nuclear arsenal is estimated to contain around 170 warheads.
title: US slaps sanctions on Pakistan over Ballistic Missile Programme

description: The Supreme Court settled a 20-year-old excise duty debate, deciding that pure coconut oil's classification depends on its branding.  If labeled and regulated as edible oil, it falls under that category, even in small packaging.  The court rejected the revenue department's argument that small containers automatically meant hair oil, emphasizing the need for clear labeling to distinguish between uses.
title: Is coconut oil hair oil or edible oil? Supreme Court solves old puzzle

description: A Delhi court granted interim bail to Umar Khalid, accused in the 2020 Delhi riots conspiracy case, for a family wedding.  The bail, with conditions including restricted movement and social media ban, allows him to attend his cousin's wedding and related ceremonies. Khalid has been in jail since September 2020.
title: In jail since 2020, Umar Khalid gets 7-day bail for family wedding

description: A speedboat collided with a ferry heading to Elephanta Caves, Mumbai, resulting in the capsizing of the ferry. Survivors recounted the chaotic scene, with passengers scrambling for life jackets. One passenger witnessed a speedboat passenger being flung onto the ferry deck upon impact. Several passengers remain missing, while survivors are being treated for injuries and trauma.

description: John Cena and Roman Reigns, two WWE icons, often spark net worth comparisons.  Cena's fortune stands at $80 million, boosted by a $10 million annual WWE salary and various ventures. description: Donald Trump has repeatedly teased Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau about making Canada the 51st US state. Trump claims the US subsidizes Canada and questions why. Trump previously linked potential tariffs to Canada's handling of immigration and trade, suggesting statehood as an alternative if the Canadian economy suffered.

description: Cricketer Ravichandran Ashwin's surprise retirement announcement after India's recent Test victory sparked an outpouring of accolades. description: Starting January 1, 2025, US nonimmigrant visa applicants can reschedule their interview once without charge.  A second rescheduling or missed appointment requires a new booking and fee repayment.  This change aims to improve appointment availability and reduce wait times, currently exceeding 400 days in major Indian cities.

description: Two Congress workers died during protests on Wednesday. Police accounts differ from Congress claims in both incidents.

description: Nithin Kamath, CEO of Zerodha, warns against a rising courier scam targeting Indians. Scammers impersonate officials, alleging illegal items in packages and threatening "digital arrest."  They leverage fear to extract personal information and money. Kamath shared a video demonstrating the scam and urged vigilance, especially among the elderly.

description: Sleep apnea disrupts breathing during sleep. This can lead to Type 2 diabetes.  Millions suffer from sleep apnea.  The link between these conditions is often overlooked.  Sleep studies diagnose sleep apnea.  Treatments include dental devices and wearables.  Screening for sleep apnea is important in diabetes detection programs. Consult a doctor if you have sleep problems.

description: Union Home Minister Amit Shah countered Congress chief Mallikarjun Kharge's resignation demand, stating Congress would remain in opposition for 15 years.  Shah accused Kharge of supporting Congress's distortion of his Ambedkar remarks under Rahul Gandhi's pressure. He highlighted BJP's commitment to Ambedkar's principles and criticized Congress's historical treatment of Ambedkar, citing delayed Bharat Ratna recognition.

description: Indian captain Rohit Sharma paid tribute to Ravichandran Ashwin after the spinner announced his retirement from Test cricket. With 765 international wickets, Ashwin concludes his Test career as India's second-highest wicket-taker, boasting 537 wickets in 106 matches.

description: The Supreme Court invited protesting farmers for discussions, but the farmers refused, demanding direct talks with the central government.  They intensified their agitation with a 'Rail Roko' protest, disrupting train services across Punjab.  Their demands include a legally binding MSP, debt waivers, and withdrawal of police cases.

description: Elon Musk denied claims that Starlink was used by terrorists in Manipur, India, after a device bearing a similar logo was found in a recovered arms cache.  Musk stated that Starlink's satellite internet beams are deactivated over India and were never operational there.  The device's authenticity and legality are questioned as Starlink lacks an operational license in India.

description: A government-appointed panel led by ex-ISRO chief K. Radhakrishnan has proposed restructuring the National Testing Agency (NTA) after the NEET UG 2024 paper leak. Recommendations include focusing solely on entrance exams from 2025, introducing computer-adaptive testing, and stricter security measures like CCTV surveillance, secure courier services, and sealed containers to prevent question paper leaks, ensuring exam integrity and transparency.

description: Veteran Indian off-spinner Ravichandran Ashwin unexpectedly announced his retirement from international cricket during the ongoing Test series against Australia. description: Congress has demanded an apology from PM Modi, Amit Shah, and the BJP, along with Shah's resignation, for allegedly insulting B.R. Ambedkar. Congress accuses the BJP-RSS of harboring contempt for Ambedkar and opposing equal rights for Dalits and the oppressed.

description: Panic gripped Rajgarh district hospital in Madhya Pradesh late Tuesday night when an oxygen supply pipe to the NICU was stolen, jeopardizing the lives of 12 newborns. The missing copper pipe disrupted oxygen flow, causing breathing difficulties and triggering alarms. description: Veteran Indian off-spinner R Ashwin on Wednesday stunned the cricketing world by announcing his retirement from international cricket after the drawn Test against Australia at the Gabba. description: R Ashwin's cricket journey, from a fringe player in the 2011 World Cup to one of India's greatest match-winners, has been marked by trials, triumphs, and unwavering dedication. description: Sunil Gavaskar questioned Ravichandran Ashwin's mid-series retirement announcement, stating it leaves India short-handed in the middle of an important series. Gavaskar compared it to Dhoni's 2014 retirement, emphasizing the disruption it causes. He pointed out the role Ashwin could have played in the remaining Tests, especially in Sydney, which offers spin-friendly conditions.

description: Delhi's AAP leader, Arvind Kejriwal, unveiled the 'Sanjivni Yojna,' promising free treatment for senior citizens if re-elected. description: Elon Musk denied Starlink's operation in India after a device bearing its logo was found during a Manipur security operation. Musk stated Starlink beams were "never on" over India. description: Asteroid 2024 XS3, a small Apollo asteroid, safely passed Earth at a distance of 3.3 million kilometers on December 18, 2024.  This close approach provided astronomers with a valuable opportunity to refine tracking techniques.  While posing no threat, 2024 XS3's observation contributes to planetary defense efforts and our understanding of the early solar system.

description: NASA's InSight lander mission on Mars has ended.  The lander studied Marsquakes and the planet's interior. Dust accumulated on its solar panels, causing power loss.  Orbiting spacecraft captured images of the dust-covered lander.  Scientists continue to analyze data from InSight.  The data includes information about dust devils and Martian weather.  NASA is no longer receiving signals from the lander.

description: Ola CEO Bhavish Aggarwal criticizes employees for poor attendance in a stern email, threatening stricter measures. This follows recent job cuts and a focus on cost efficiency as the company aims to boost profitability and expand its store network significantly.

description: During the Gabba Test, Virat Kohli masterminded Travis Head's dismissal, despite Australia's 201-run lead. Siraj executed the plan perfectly, forcing Head into a mistimed pull shot, caught by Rishabh Pant.

description: A Delhi court granted interim bail for seven days to former JNU student Umar Khalid in the Delhi riots conspiracy case, allowing him to attend a family wedding.  Khalid's lawyer questioned his inclusion as an accused, highlighting that others present at alleged conspiracy meetings weren't charged, despite some meetings being publicly documented on social media.

description: Uttarakhand will become the first Indian state to implement the Uniform Civil Code (UCC) starting January 2025.  The law mandates marriage registration within six months and requires live-in couples to register within one month.  The UCC addresses marriage, divorce, inheritance, and live-in relationships, aiming to end practices like polygamy and ensure equal inheritance rights.
title: UCC will be implemented in Uttarakhand from Jan 2025: CM Dhami

description: Following the Brisbane Test, Indian captain Rohit Sharma humorously addressed media inquiries about veteran players Cheteshwar Pujara and Ajinkya Rahane. description: R Ashwin announced his retirement from international cricket, sharing an emotional moment with captain Rohit Sharma during the press conference. Ashwin concluded his international career with 537 Test wickets, 156 ODI wickets and 72 T20I wickets.
title: 'Bit of punch still left in me' - says retired Ashwin

description: In the third Test of the Border-Gavaskar Trophy at The Gabba, Brisbane, Mohammed Siraj dismissed Steve Smith for a low score, leaving Australia struggling at 33/5 in their second innings. Following India's first innings total of 260, Virat Kohli's tactical advice to Siraj proved crucial in Smith's dismissal.
title: Watch: How Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma worked out Steve Smith's dismissal

description: MobiKwik's shares surged 85% on their debut, valuing the company around Rs 40 billion.  The successful $67 million IPO, oversubscribed by 120 times, highlights the booming fintech sector in India.  This contrasts with the broader market's decline, with Sensex and Nifty dipping amid foreign fund outflows and pre-Fed decision caution.
title: MobiKwik's shares jump 85% on trading debut, valued at Rs 40 billion

description: Hyderabadis eager to see Coldplay in Ahmedabad face soaring airfares, with round-trip tickets reaching ₹43,000, nearly four times the usual price.  Over 3,000 fans from the city are expected to attend, driving up demand and pushing some to seek alternative routes through Surat or even road trips to mitigate the inflated travel costs.
title: Up & Up: Coldplay sends airfares from Hyderabad to Ahmedabad soaring

description: Intel's interim leadership hints at potential restructuring, including a possible separation of manufacturing and product development.  Facing challenges from competitors like AMD, particularly in data centers and AI, Intel acknowledges performance issues and emphasizes long-term investment over short-term gains.
title: Breaking up of Intel: Interim CEO says that's an open question for...

description: A Kamaka Air Cessna 208 Caravan crashed into a vacant building near Honolulu's airport during a training flight, tragically killing both crew members on board. The pilot reported a loss of control shortly before the impact.  The FAA is investigating the cause of this devastating incident.
title: Video: Plane goes 'out of control' in Hawaii, crashes into building killing 2

description: Nine-year-old Sri Tej, injured in the Hyderabad stampede at a Pushpa 2 premiere, suffered severe brain damage.  Police Commissioner CV Anand and health secretary Christina Z Chongthu visited Sri Tej, assuring government support for his medical care at KIMS Hospitals.  His mother, Revathi, tragically died in the incident.
title: 'Pushpa 2' stampede: Injured 9-year-old has severe brain damage

description: Delhi's air quality plummeted to 'severe' on Wednesday, with a thick fog and a minimum temperature of 5°C. The AQI reached 442, impacting visibility and causing breathing difficulties.  GRAP Stage IV measures remain in effect as residents experience worsening pollution, prompting calls for action.
title: Delhi's air quality 'severe' at 442, temperature drops to 5 degrees Celsius

description: Chinese fast-fashion giant Shein will return to India through a partnership with Reliance Retail, following a 2020 ban.  Shein will act as a technology provider, while Reliance Retail controls operations and data, ensuring all information remains within India under strict security measures. This collaboration aims to boost local manufacturing and create jobs.
title: Reliance is bringing back Shein products in India; but with a Big Desi twist

description: India's Test captain Rohit Sharma's poor run of form has continued in the Border Gavaskar Trophy.  Batting legend Sunil Gavaskar speculates that Rohit might step down as captain if his struggles persist in the remaining Tests.  Meanwhile, Cheteshwar Pujara suggests that Rohit's decision to not open may be contributing to his difficulties.
title: Rohit 'himself will step down if doesn't score' in next two Tests

description: Vinicius Jr. and Aitana Bonmati secured FIFA's top player honours at The Best Awards 2024. Vinicius's instrumental role in Real Madrid's LaLiga and Champions League victories earned him the men's award, while Bonmati's contributions to Barcelona's treble and Spain's Nations League triumph led her to retain the women's title. Carlo Ancelotti and Emma Hayes were recognised as the best coaches.
title: FIFA The Best Awards 2024: Complete list of winners

description: Russia announces the development of an mRNA cancer vaccine, slated for a 2025 launch.  Pre-clinical trials demonstrate tumor suppression and metastasis reduction.  AI integration promises to personalize vaccine creation within an hour, significantly accelerating the current lengthy process. The vaccine aims to bolster the immune system's ability to target and eliminate cancer cells.
title: Russia develops cancer vaccine, to be distributed free of charge

description: Astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore's ISS mission has been extended until late March due to technical glitches with Boeing's Starliner and delays in the next SpaceX Crew Dragon launch. Originally scheduled to return in February 2025 after their June 2024 arrival, the duo will now spend approximately ten months in space.
title: Nasa delays rescue mission again: Sunita Williams to stay on ISS until March

description: A fire in a rented house in Kathua, Jammu and Kashmir, tragically killed six people and injured four others, including a neighbor who assisted in rescue efforts.  The victims, residing in the home of a retired DSP, likely died from suffocation.  Authorities are investigating the incident and will release the bodies after post-mortems are conducted.
title: J&K: 6 dead, 4 injured after fire breaks out at retired DSP's house in Kathua

description: NCP MLA Chhagan Bhujbal expressed his discontent over being excluded from the Maharashtra cabinet despite CM Fadnavis, Praful Patel, and Sunil Tatkare's efforts. Bhujbal criticized Ajit Pawar's decision-making process and rejected a Rajya Sabha nomination, prioritizing his constituents' wishes. He plans to consult with community members before deciding his political future.
title: 'One-man show': Bhujbal slams Ajit Pawar for denying cabinet berth

description: President-elect Donald Trump reaffirmed his commitment to imposing reciprocal taxes on India, citing high tariffs on American goods.  He emphasized that if India imposes tariffs, the US will respond in kind.  While trade tensions are anticipated, India could potentially benefit from trade diversions caused by Trump's tariff policies targeting other nations.
title: 'They charge a lot': Donald Trump threatens reciprocal tariffs against India

description: China and India are preparing for high-level talks aimed at improving bilateral relations.  The meeting between NSA Ajit Doval and Chinese Foreign Minister Wang Yi will focus on border issues, including finding a resolution to the boundary question.  This follows recent disengagement agreements and patrolling arrangements along the Line of Actual Control (LAC) after a prolonged standoff.
title: 'Ready to work with India': China ahead of key meet between Ajit Doval and Wang Yi

description: Rain and lightning disruptions continued to plague the third India-Australia Test at the Gabba. Australia quickly took the final Indian wicket, securing a 185-run lead. However, lightning and subsequent rain forced play to be suspended. A 30-second rule, based on the time between lightning flash and thunderclap, dictates play suspension as per ICC protocols.
title: Explained: The '30:30 rule' in cricket for lightning stopping play

description: Allu Arjun's "Pushpa 2" continues its box office reign, crossing ₹953.3 crore in just 13 days.  The film's impressive opening day haul of ₹164.25 crore propelled it past ₹700 crore in its first week.  Steady weekday earnings indicate a strong trajectory towards the ₹1000 crore club.  OTT release on Netflix is anticipated in February 2025.
title: Pushpa 2 inches toward the Rs 1000 crore club in India

description: India's fightback in the third Test against Australia at the Gabba ended with a humorous incident involving Akash Deep. After a defiant last-wicket stand with Jasprit Bumrah, Deep mistakenly dropped the ball at Travis Head's feet after it lodged in his pads. He apologized, but was stumped shortly after, giving Australia a 185-run lead.
title: Watch: Akash Deep says 'sorry sorry' after irritating Travis Head

description: Hindi-language film 'Santosh' has been shortlisted for the Best International Feature Film at the 2025 Oscars. Representing the UK, the film, directed by Sandhya Suri and starring Shahana as a widowed police constable, premiered at Cannes to critical acclaim. Selected from 85 submissions, 'Santosh' explores themes of corruption and murder in rural North India.
title: India's 'Laapataa Ladies' out of Oscars 2025; UK's Hindi film 'Santosh' shortlisted

description: Luigi Mangione has been indicted on 11 counts, including terrorism-related murder, for the shooting death of UnitedHealth executive Brian Thompson in Manhattan. Prosecutors allege Mangione's act was premeditated and intended to influence government policy. The Ivy League-educated Mangione was apprehended in Pennsylvania after a five-day manhunt and is awaiting extradition to New York.
title: Luigi Mangione indicted for murder of UnitedHealthcare CEO

description: Ronda Rousey's journey in love began with MMA fighter Timothy DiGorrio (2012-2013), followed by a relationship with Brendan Schaub (2013-2014).  She found lasting love with Travis Browne, marrying him in 2017.  They welcomed their daughter in 2021 and announced a second pregnancy in 2024, sharing their story of love, loss, and parenthood.
title: Past relationships of ex-WWE Women's Champion Ronda Rousey

description: Dominique Pelicot, a 72-year-old man, was convicted in France for orchestrating the rape of his wife, Gisele, over 200 times by 70 men. He used an online dating platform to lure the men and drugged Gisele before the assaults, which occurred over a decade. Pelicot's crimes came to light after his arrest for filming upskirts.
title: How Dominique Pelicot organised the mass rape of his wife

description: Popeye and Tintin's early versions enter the US public domain in 2025, allowing their use without copyright restrictions.  However, later additions like Popeye's spinach and Tintin's signature colors remain protected.  Literary classics by Faulkner, Hemingway, and Steinbeck also join the public domain.
title: Popeye, Tintin in public domain from 2025... but minus spinach & red hair
Naga group 'temporarily' accepts govt's autonomy offer
Cannon rebound during drill leads to jawan's death
Congress wants 50% cap off to give Muslims quota: Amit Shah

description: Four doctors, including an NSG Major, were arrested and sent to judicial remand in Gurgaon for assaulting a police officer at a Karan Aujla concert.  The doctors, who allegedly tried to enter through the exit gate, argued with security and then with the Bhondsi inspector, tearing his uniform. They were charged with assault, obstructing a public servant, and false personation.
title: NSG officer among 4 held for assaulting cop at rapper Karan Aujla’s event
Goa CM’s wife files Rs 100cr defamation suit against AAP MP Sanjay Singh

description: A Bengaluru court convicted three Bhatkal youths for plotting nationwide blasts during President Obama's 2015 India visit.  The plot, involving explosives and links to Pakistan, was uncovered during the Church Street blast investigation. Two other suspects were acquitted.
title: Barack Obama’s 2015 visit: 3 from Bhatkal convicted for terror plot

description: Tech giants, including Amazon, Meta, and OpenAI, are donating millions to Donald Trump's inaugural fund, marking a shift in their previously distant relationships.  Elon Musk reacted with amusement.  These donations come as CEOs seek meetings at Mar-a-Lago, aiming to navigate potential regulatory challenges under the new administration. Trump welcomed the outreach, eager for input from business leaders.
title: Why Elon Musk responded with 'LMAO' on post about Microsoft, Amazon CEOs
